I was not able to disable completely the dark mode on widget. What did I do was to changed the colors of the widget to better handle the UI and the UX.

In the widget view controller you have to handle the change to dark mode like this
`
    var isDarkMode = false

    override func willTransition(to newCollection: UITraitCollection, with coordinator: UIViewControllerTransitionCoordinator) {
        super.willTransition(to: newCollection, with: coordinator)
        
        if #available(iOS 12.0, *) {
            if (newCollection.userInterfaceStyle == .dark) {
                isDarkMode = true
                
            } else {
                isDarkMode = false
            }
        } else {
            isDarkMode = false
        }
    }
`

please note also that the isDarkMode flag must be initialised somewhere in your code on the starting status of the device

            isDarkMode = (self.traitCollection.userInterfaceStyle == .dark)

once you know that you are in dark mode you can probably redesign the UI to be with the colors you prefer.

HTH

