&gt; Can imagedefinitions.json be used to specify an existing task definition?&lt;br&gt;

The “imagedefinitions.json” file does not define an ECS task. It defines a container_name (part of an ECS Task Definition) and image_name:tag.

    [
      {
        &quot;name&quot;: &quot;sample-app&quot;,
        &quot;imageUri&quot;: &quot;11111EXAMPLE.dkr.ecr.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/ecs-repo:latest&quot;
      }
    ]



In an ECS Deploy action, you specify the cluster name and service name. Add the two items from “imagedefinitions.json” i.e. container_name and image:tag and ECS job worker has all the information it needs to create a Task Definition revision and update a Service (a service has an associated task definition).

**ECS Deploy Action definition in a Pipeline:**

          {
                &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Deploy&quot;,
                &quot;actions&quot;: [
                    {
                        &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Deploy&quot;,
                        &quot;actionTypeId&quot;: {
                            &quot;category&quot;: &quot;Deploy&quot;,
                            &quot;owner&quot;: &quot;AWS&quot;,
                            &quot;provider&quot;: &quot;ECS&quot;,
                            &quot;version&quot;: &quot;1&quot;
                        },
                        &quot;runOrder&quot;: 1,
                        &quot;roleArn&quot;: &quot;arn:aws:iam::&lt;Account&gt;:role/Pipeline_Role&quot;,
                        &quot;configuration&quot;: {
                            &quot;ClusterName&quot;: &quot;&lt;Cluster&gt;&quot;,     &lt;====================
                            &quot;ServiceName&quot;: &quot;&lt;Service&gt;”      &lt;====================
                        },
                        &quot;outputArtifacts&quot;: [],
                        &quot;inputArtifacts&quot;: [
                            {
                                &quot;name&quot;: &quot;SourceArtifact&quot;
                            }
                        ],
                        &quot;region&quot;: &quot;us-east-1&quot;
                    }
                ]
            }

&lt;br&gt;
Note that the result of Deploy stage using ECS Deploy action is a new Task definition revision that will include the updated Image URI for the specified container in the task definition. Your other task definition parameters (e.g. environment variables) should remain unchanged.



&gt; Or, can I specify environmental variables in this file?&lt;br&gt;

No, but as discussed above, your existing Task Def (the TaskDef from which a new revision is created) environment variables will remain as it is.

Let me know if there is any confusion.

